Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodiian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '4̣6̣'. Name Klenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0165.08.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (114)
